Otis Spann (March 21, 1924 or 1930 â€“ April 24, 1970) was an American blues musician, whom many consider to be the leading postwar Chicago blues pianist.

Some state that he was born in Jackson, Mississippi, in 1930, but the researchers Bob Eagle and Eric LeBlanc concluded, on the basis of census records and other official information, that he was born in 1924 in Belzoni, Mississippi.
